Checklist before moving to Day 6 (Review & Rating, Admin)


 POST /internal/notifications works directly and returns a SENT notification

 Registering a delivery partner with the wrong role (e.g. a CUSTOMER user_id) is rejected

 POST /api/deliveries fails with NoPartnerAvailableException when no partner is AVAILABLE + APPROVED, and succeeds once one is

 Moving a delivery to PICKED_UP then DELIVERED correctly moves orders.order_status in step, verified by checking Order Service directly

 Killing Notification Service and creating a delivery still succeeds (best-effort notification, not a hard dependency)

 GET /internal/deliveries/by-order/{orderId} works directly — Review Service will use this on Day 6 to confirm which partner handled a completed order


Day 6 (Review & Rating Service, Admin Service) will be the last two services — Review Service Feign-calls Order Service (to confirm DELIVERED status) and this new Delivery endpoint; Admin Service mostly orchestrates calls into Restaurant/Delivery/Auth Service rather than owning much data itself.

